# .secretsignore.default — hypomnema-managed allowlist for the
# memory-secrets-detect hook. Overwritten on upgrade; DO NOT EDIT.
#
# For your own patterns create ~/.claude/memory/.secretsignore.
# Both files use a minimal subset of .gitignore syntax:
#   - one pattern per line
#   - `#` comments
#   - `!pattern` negates (un-ignore) a previous match
#   - `**` matches any number of path segments
#   - `*` matches any characters within a single segment
#
# Paths are matched relative to $CLAUDE_MEMORY_DIR.

# Seed files ship with realistic "what NOT to do" examples
# (git-committed-secrets-history, etc.) that the detector would
# otherwise flag. They are documentation of hazards, not hazards.
seeds/**
